  sectionId (33774)
  sectionNo (264)
  orderNo 265
  title `Jurisdiction of District Judge in granting and revoking probates, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_264_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_264_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33774&sectionno=264&orderno=265&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_264_content:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_264_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_265:
  sectionId (33775)
  sectionNo (265)
  orderNo 266
  title `Power to appoint delegate of District Judge to deal with non-contentious cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_265_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_265_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33775&sectionno=265&orderno=266&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_265_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `High Court may appoint such judicial officers within any district as it thinks fit to act for the District`
  line `Judge as delegates to grant probate and letters of administration in non-contentious cases, within such`
  line `local limits as it may prescribe:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in the case of High Courts not established by Royal Charter, such appointments shall`
  line `not be without the previous sanction of the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Persons so appointed shall be called "District Delegates".`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of Central Act 39 of 1925.--In the Indian Succession Act, 1925 (Central Act 39 of`
  line `1925) as in force in the State of Karnataka, section 265 shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 28 of 1978, s. 4].`
obj_root_law_sections_265_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_266:
  sectionId (33776)
  sectionNo (266)
  orderNo 267
  title `District Judge’s powers as to grant of probate and administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_266_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_266_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33776&sectionno=266&orderno=267&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_266_content:
  string
  line `The District Judge shall`
  line `have the like powers and authority in relation to the granting of probate and letters of administration and`
  line `all matters connected therewith, as are by law vested in him in relation to any civil suit or proceeding`
  line `pending in his Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_266_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_267:
  sectionId (33777)
  sectionNo (267)
  orderNo 268
  title `District Judge may order person to produce testamentary papers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_267_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_267_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33777&sectionno=267&orderno=268&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_267_content:
  string
  line `(1) The District Judge`
  line `may order any person to produce and bring into Court any paper or writing, being or purporting to be`
  line `testamentary, which may be shown to be in the possession or under the control of such person.`
  line
  line `(2) If it is not shown that any such paper or writing is in the possession or under the control of such`
  line `person, but there is reason to believe that he has the knowledge of any such paper or writing, the Court`
  line `may direct such person to attend for the purpose of being examined respecting the same.`
  line
  line `(3) Such person shall be bound to answer truly such question as may be put to him by the Court, and,`
  line `if so ordered, to produce and bring in such paper or writing, and shall be subject to the like punishment`
  line `under the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), in case of default in not attending or in not answering such`
  line `question or not bringing in such paper or writing, as he would have been subject to in case he had been a`
  line `party to a suit and had made such default.`
  line
  line `(4) The costs of the proceeding shall be in the discretion of the Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_267_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_268:
  sectionId (33778)
  sectionNo (268)
  orderNo 269
  title `Proceedings of District Judge’s Court in relation to probate and administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_268_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_268_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33778&sectionno=268&orderno=269&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_268_content:
  string
  line The
  line `proceeding of the Court of the District Judge in relation to the granting of probate and letters of`
  line `administration shall, save as hereinafter otherwise provided, be regulated, so far as the circumstances of`
  line `the case permit, by the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908).`
obj_root_law_sections_268_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_269:
  sectionId (33779)
  sectionNo (269)
  orderNo 270
  title `When and how District Judge to interfere for protection of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_269_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_269_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33779&sectionno=269&orderno=270&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_269_content:
  string
  line `(1) Until probate is`
  line `granted of the will of a deceased person, or an administrator of his estate is constituted, the District Judge,`
  line `within whose jurisdiction any part of the property of the deceased person is situate, is authorised and`
  line `required to interfere for the protection of such property at the instance of any person claiming to be`
  line `interested therein, and in all other cases where the Judge considers that the property incurs any risk of loss`
  line `or damage; and for that purpose, if he thinks fit, to appoint an officer to take and keep possession of the`
  line property,
  line
  line `(2) This section shall not apply when the deceased' is a Hindu, Muhammadan, Buddhist, Sikh or Jaina`
  line `or an exempted person, nor shall it apply to any part of the property of an Indian Christian who has died`
  line intestate.
obj_root_law_sections_269_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_270:
  sectionId (33780)
  sectionNo (270)
  orderNo 271
  title `When probate or administration may be granted by District Judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_270_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_270_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33780&sectionno=270&orderno=271&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_270_content:
  string
  line `Probate of the will or`
  line `letters of administration to the estate of a deceased person may be granted by a District Judge under the`
  line `seal of his Court, if it appears by a petition, verified as hereinafter provided, of the person applying for the`
  line `same that the testator or intestate, as the case may be, at the time of his decease had a fixed place of`
  line `abode, or any property, moveable or immoveable, within the jurisdiction of the Ridge.`
obj_root_law_sections_270_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_271:
  sectionId (33781)
  sectionNo (271)
  orderNo 272
  title `Disposal of application made to Judge of district in which deceased had no fixed abode.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_271_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_271_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33781&sectionno=271&orderno=272&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_271_content:
  string
  line `When the application is made to the Judge of a district in which the deceased had no fixed abode at the`
  line `time of his death, it shall be in the discretion of the Judge to refuse the application, if in his judgment it`
  line `could be disposed of more justly or conveniently in another district, or, where the application is for letters`
  line `of administration, to grant them absolutely, or limited to the property within his own jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_271_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_272:
  sectionId (33782)
  sectionNo (272)
  orderNo 273
  title `Probate and letters of administration may be granted by Delegate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_272_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_272_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33782&sectionno=272&orderno=273&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_272_content:
  string
  line `Probate and letters of`
  line `administration may, upon application for that purpose to any District Delegate, be granted by him in any`
  line `case in which there is no contention, if it appears by petition, verified as hereinafter provided, that the`
  line `testator or intestate, as the case may be, at the time of his death had a fixed place of abode within the`
  line `jurisdiction of such Delegate.`
obj_root_law_sections_272_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_273:
  sectionId (33783)
  sectionNo (273)
  orderNo 274
  title `Conclusiveness of probate or letters of administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_273_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_273_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33783&sectionno=273&orderno=274&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_273_content:
  string
  line `Probate or letters of administration`
  line `shall have effect over all the property and estate, moveable or immoveable, of the deceased, throughout`
  line `the State in which the same is or are granted, and shall be conclusive as to the representative title against`
  line `all debtors of the deceased, and all persons holding property which belongs to him, and shall afford full`
  line `indemnity to all debtors, paying their debts and all persons delivering up such property to the person to`
  line `whom such probate or letters of administration have been granted:`
  line
  line `Provided that probates and letters of administration granted--`
  line
  line `(a) by a High Court, or`
  line
  line `(b) by a District Judge, where the deceased at the time of his death had a fixed place of abode`
  line `situate within the jurisdiction of such Judge, and such Judge certifies that the value of the property`
  line `and estate affected beyond the limits of the State does not exceed ten thousand rupees, shall, unless`
  line `otherwise directed by the grant, have like effect throughout ^1[the other States ^2***.]`
  line
  line `^3[The proviso to this section shall apply in ^4[India]^5`
  line `after the separation of Burma and Aden from`
  line `India to probates and letters of administration granted in Burma and Aden before the date of the`
  line `separation, or after that date in proceedings which were pending at that date.]`
  line
  line `^6[The proviso shall also apply in ^4[India] ^7*** ^8`
  line `after the separation of Pakistan from India to probates`
  line `and letters of administration granted before the date of the separation, or after that date in procedings`
  line `pending at that date, in any of the territories which on that date constituted Pakistan.]`
obj_root_law_sections_273_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1948, for "the whole of British India" .`
  line
  line `2. The words of "India" omitted by the A.O. 1950.`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and Sch., for "the States".`
  line
  line `5. 1st April, 1937.`
  line
  line `6. Added by the A.O. 1948.`
  line
  line `7. The words "of India" omitted by Act 42 of 1953, s. 4 and Sch. III.`
  line
  line `8. 15th August, 1947.`
obj_root_law_sections_274:
  sectionId (33784)
  sectionNo (274)
  orderNo 275
  title `Transmission to High Courts of certificate of grants under proviso to section 273.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_274_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_274_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33784&sectionno=274&orderno=275&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_274_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where probate or letters of administration has or have been granted by a High Court or District Judge`
  line `with the effect referred to in the proviso to section 273, the High Court or District Judge shall send a`
  line `certificate thereof to the following Courts, namely:-`
  line
  line `(a) when the grant has been made by a High Court, to each of the other High Courts;`
  line
  line `(b) when the grant has been made by a District Judge, to the High Court to which such District`
  line `Judge is subordinate and to each of the other High Courts.`
  line
  line `(2) Every certificate referred to in sub-section (1) shall be made as nearly as circumstances admit in`
  line `the form set forth in Schedule IV, and such certificate shall be filed by the High Court receiving the same.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any portion of the assets has been stated by the petitioner, as hereinafter provided in`
  line `sections 276 and 278, to be situate within the jurisdiction of a District Judge in another State, the Court`
  line `required to send the certificate referred to in sub-section (1) shall send a copy thereof to such District`
  line `Judge, and such copy shall be filed by the District Judge receiving the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_274_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_275:
  sectionId (33785)
  sectionNo (275)
  orderNo 276
  title `Conclusiveness of application for probate or administration if properly made and verified.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_275_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_275_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33785&sectionno=275&orderno=276&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_275_content:
  string
  line `The application for probate or letters of administration, if made and verified in the manner`
  line `hereinafter provided, shall be conclusive for the purpose of authorising the grant of probate or`
  line `administration; and no such grant shall be impeached by reason only that the testator or intestate had no`
  line `fixed place of abode or no property within the district at the time of his death, unless by a proceeding to`
  line `revoke the grant if obtained by a fraud upon the Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_275_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_276:
  sectionId (33786)
  sectionNo (276)
  orderNo 277
  title `Petition for probate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_276_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_276_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33786&sectionno=276&orderno=277&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_276_content:
  string
  line `(1) Application for probate or for letters of administration, with the will`
  line `annexed, shall be made by a petition distinctly written in English or in the language in ordinary use in`
  line `proceedings before the Court in which the application is made, with the will or, in the cases mentioned in`
  line `sections 237, 238 and 239, a copy, draft, or statement of the contents thereof, annexed, and stating`
  line
  line `(a) the time of the testators death,`
  line
  line `(b) that the writing annexed is his last will and testament,`
  line
  line `(c) that it was duly executed,`
  line
  line `(d) the amount of assets which are likely to come to the petitioner's hands, and`
  line
  line `(e) when the application is for probate, that the petitioner is the executor named in the will.`
  line
  line `(2) In addition to these particulars, the petition shall further state,--`
  line
  line `(a) when the application is to the District Judge, that the deceased at the time of his death had a`
  line `fixed place of abode, or had some property, situate within the jusrisdiction of the Judge; and`
  line
  line `(b) when the application is to a District Delegate, that the deceased at the time of his death had a`
  line `fixed place of abode within the jurisdiction of such Delegate.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the application is to the District Judge and any portion of the assets likely to come to the`
  line `petitioner's hands is situate in another State, the petition shall further state the amount of such assets in`
  line `each State and the District Judges within whose jurisdiction such assets are situate.`
obj_root_law_sections_276_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_277:
  sectionId (33787)
  sectionNo (277)
  orderNo 278
  title `In what cases translation of will to be annexed to petition. Verification of translation by person other than Court translator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_277_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_277_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33787&sectionno=277&orderno=278&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_277_content:
  string
  line `In cases wherein the will, copy or draft, is written in any`
  line `language other than English or than that in ordinary use in proceedings before the Court, there shall be a`
  line `translation thereof annexed to the petition by a translator of the Court, if the language be one for which a`
  line `translator is appointed; or, if the will, copy or draft, is in any other language, then by any person`
  line `competent to translate the same, in which case such translation shall be verified by that person in the`
  line `following manner, namely:--`
  line
  line `"I (A.B.) do declare that I read and perfectly understand the language and character of the`
  line `original, and that the above is a true and accurate translation thereof."`
obj_root_law_sections_277_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_278:
  sectionId (33788)
  sectionNo (278)
  orderNo 279
  title `Petition for letters of administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_278_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_278_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33788&sectionno=278&orderno=279&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_278_content:
  string
  line `(1) Application for letters of administration shall be`
  line `made by petition distinctly written as aforesaid and stating-`
  line
  line `(a) the time and place of the deceased's death;`
  line
  line `(b) the family or other relatives of the deceased, and their respective residences;`
  line
  line `(c) the right in which the petitioner claims;`
  line
  line `(d) the amount of assets which are likely to come to the petitioner's hands;`
  line
  line `(e) when the application is to the District Judge, that the deceased at the time of his death had a`
  line `fixed place of abode, or had some property, situate within the jurisdiction of the Judge; and`
  line
  line `(f) when the application is to a District Delegate, that the deceased at the time of his death had a`
  line `fixed place of abode within the jurisdiction of such Delegate.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the application is to the District Judge and any portion of the assets likely to come to the`
  line `petitioner's hands is situate in another State, the petition shall further state the amount of such assets in`
  line `each State and the District Judges within whose jurisdiction such assets are situate.`
obj_root_law_sections_278_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_279:
  sectionId (33789)
  sectionNo (279)
  orderNo 280
  title `Addition to statement in petition, etc., for probate or letters of administration in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_279_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "the States".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33789&sectionno=279&orderno=280&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_279_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person applying to any of the Courts mentioned in the proviso to section 273 for`
  line `probate of a will or letters of administration of an estate intended to have effect throughout ^1[India], shall`
  line `state in his petition, in addition to the matters respectively required by section 276 and section 278, that to`
  line `the best of his belief no application has been made to any other Court for a probate of the same will or for`
  line `letters of administration of the same estate, intended to have such effect as last aforesaid,`
  line
  line `or, where any such application has been made, the Court to which it was made, the person or persons by`
  line `whom it was made and the proceedings (if any) had thereon.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court to which any such application is made under the proviso to section 273 may, if it thinks`
  line `fit, reject the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_280:
  sectionId (33790)
  sectionNo (280)
  orderNo 281
  title `Petition for probate, etc., to be signed and verified.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_280_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_280_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33790&sectionno=280&orderno=281&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_280_content:
  string
  line `The petition for probate or letters of`
  line `administration shall in all cases be subscribed by the petitioner and his pleader, if any, and shall be`
  line `verified by the petitioner in the following manner, namely:--`
  line
  line `"I (A.B.), the petitioner in the above petition, declare that what is stated therein is true to the best`
  line `of my information and belief."`
obj_root_law_sections_280_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_281:
  sectionId (33791)
  sectionNo (281)
  orderNo 282
  title `Verification of petition for probate, by one witness to will.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_281_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_281_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33791&sectionno=281&orderno=282&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_281_content:
  string
  line `Where the application is for`
  line `probate, the petition shall also be verified by at least one of the witnesses to the will (when procurable) in`
  line `the manner or to the effect following, namely:--`
  line
  line `"I (C.D.), one of the witnesses to the last will and testament of the testator mentioned in the above`
  line `petition, declare that I was present and saw the said testator affix his signature (or mark) thereto (or`
  line `that the said testator acknowledged the writing annexed to the above petition to be his last will and`
  line `testament in my presence)."`
obj_root_law_sections_281_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_282:
  sectionId (33792)
  sectionNo (282)
  orderNo 283
  title `Punishment for false averment in petition or declaration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_282_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_282_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33792&sectionno=282&orderno=283&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_282_content:
  string
  line `If any petition or declaration`
  line `which is hereby required to be verified contains any averment which the person making the verification`
  line `knows or believes to be false, such person shall be deemed to have committed an offence under section`
  line `193 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_282_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_283:
  sectionId (33793)
  sectionNo (283)
  orderNo 284
  title `Powers of District Judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_283_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_283_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33793&sectionno=283&orderno=284&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_283_content:
  string
  line `(1) In all cases the District Judge or District Delegate may, if he`
  line `thinks proper,--`
  line
  line `(a) examine the petitioner in person, upon oath;`
  line
  line `(b) require further evidence of the due execution of the will or the right of the petitioner to the`
  line `letters of administration, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(c) issue citations calling upon all persons claiming to have any interest in the estate of the`
  line `deceased to come and see the proceedings before the grant of probate or letters of administration.`
  line
  line `(2) The citation shall be fixed up in some conspicuous part of the courthouse, and also in the office of`
  line `the Collector of the district and otherwise published or made known in such manner as the Judge or`
  line `District Delegate issuing the same may direct.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any portion of the assets has been stated by the petitioner to be situate within the`
  line `jurisdiction of a District Judge in another State, the District Judge issuing the same shall cause a copy of`
  line `the citation to be sent to such other District Judge, who shall publish the same in the same manner as if it`
  line `were a citation issued by himself, and shall certify such publication to the District Judge who issued the`
  line citation.
obj_root_law_sections_283_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_284:
  sectionId (33794)
  sectionNo (284)
  orderNo 285
  title `Caveats against grant of probate or administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_284_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_284_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33794&sectionno=284&orderno=285&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_284_content:
  string
  line `(1) Caveats against the grant of probate`
  line `or administration may be lodged with the District Judge or a District Delegate.`
  line
  line `(2) Immediately on any caveat being lodged with any District Delegate, he shall send copy thereof to`
  line `the District Judge.`
  line
  line `(3) Immediately on a caveat being entered with the District Judge, a copy thereof shall be given to the`
  line `District Delegate, if any, within whose jurisdiction it is alleged the deceased had a fixed place of abode at`
  line `the time of his death, and to any other Judge or District Delegate to whom it may appear to the District`
  line `Judge expedient to transmit the same.`
  line
  line `Form of caveat--(4) The caveat shall be made as nearly as circumstances admit in the form set forth`
  line `in Schedule V.`
obj_root_law_sections_284_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_285:
  sectionId (33795)
  sectionNo (285)
  orderNo 286
  title `After entry of caveat, no proceeding taken on petition until after notice to caveator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_285_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_285_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33795&sectionno=285&orderno=286&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_285_content:
  string
  line No
  line `proceeding shall be taken on a petition for probate or letters of administration after a caveat against the`
  line `grant thereof has been entered with the Judge or District Delegate to whom the application has been made`
  line `or notice has been given of its entry with some other Delegate, until after such notice to the person by`
  line `whom the same has been entered as the Court may think reasonable.`
obj_root_law_sections_285_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_286:
  sectionId (33796)
  sectionNo (286)
  orderNo 287
  title `District Delegate when not to grant probate or administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_286_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_286_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33796&sectionno=286&orderno=287&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_286_content:
  string
  line `A District Delegate shall`
  line `not grant probate or letters of administration in any case in which there is contention as to the grant, or in`
  line `which it otherwise appears to him that probate or letters of administration ought not to be granted in his`
  line Court.
  line
  line `Explanation.-- "Contention" means the appearance of any one in person, or by his recognized agent,`
  line `or by a pleader duly appointee to act on his behalf, to oppose the proceeding.`
obj_root_law_sections_286_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_287:
  sectionId (33797)
  sectionNo (287)
  orderNo 288
  title `Power to transmit statement to District Judge in doubtful cases where no contention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_287_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_287_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33797&sectionno=287&orderno=288&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_287_content:
  string
  line `In every case in which there is no contention, but it appears to the District Delegate`
  line `doubtful whether the probate or letters of administration should or should not be granted, or when any`
  line `question arises in relation to the grant, or application for the grant, of any probate or letters of`
  line `administration, the District Delegate may, if he thinks proper, transmit a statement of the matter in`
  line `question to the District Judge, who may direct the District Delegate to proceed in the matter of the`
  line `application, according to such instructions as to the Judge may seem necessary, or may forbid any further`
  line `proceeding by the District Delegate in relation to the matter of such application, leaving the party`
  line `applying for the grant in question to make application to the Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_287_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_288:
  sectionId (33798)
  sectionNo (288)
  orderNo 289
  title `Procedure where there is contention of District Delegate thinks probate or letters of administration should be refused in his Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_288_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_288_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33798&sectionno=288&orderno=289&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_288_content:
  string
  line `In every case in which there is contention, or the`
  line `District Delegate is of opinion that the probate or letters of administration should be refused in his Court,`
  line `the petition, with any documents which may have been filed therewith, shall be returned to the person by`
  line `whom the application was made, in order that the same may be presented to the District Judge, unless the`
  line `District Delegate thinks it necessary, for the purposes of justice, to impound the same, which he is hereby`
  line `authorised to do; and, in that case, the same shall be sent by him to the District Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_288_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_289:
  sectionId (33799)
  sectionNo (289)
  orderNo 290
  title `Grant of probate to be under seal of Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_289_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_289_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33799&sectionno=289&orderno=290&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_289_content:
  string
  line `When it appears to the District Judge or District`
  line `Delegate that probate of a will should be granted, he shall grant the same under the seal of his Court in the`
  line `form set forth in Schedule VI.`
obj_root_law_sections_289_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_290:
  sectionId (33800)
  sectionNo (290)
  orderNo 291
  title `Grant of letters of administration to be under seal of Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_290_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_290_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33800&sectionno=290&orderno=291&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_290_content:
  string
  line `When it appears to the District`
  line `Judge or District Delegate that letters of administration to the estate of a person deceased, with or without`
  line `a copy of the will annexed, should be granted, he shall grant the same under the seal of his Court in the`
  line `form set forth in Schedule VII.`
obj_root_law_sections_290_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_291:
  sectionId (33801)
  sectionNo (291)
  orderNo 292
  title Administration-bond
  content obj_root_law_sections_291_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_291_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33801&sectionno=291&orderno=292&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_291_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person to whom any grant of letters of administration, other`
  line `than a grant under section 241, is committed, shall give a bond to the District Judge with one or more`
  line `surety or sureties, engaging for the due collection, getting in, and administering the estate of the deceased,`
  line `which bond shall be in such form as the Judge may, by general or special order, direct.`
  line
  line `(2) When the deceased was a Hindu, Muhammadan, Buddhist, Sikh or Jaina or an exempted person--`
  line
  line `(a) the exception made by sub-section (1) in respect of a grant under section 241 shall not`
  line operate.
  line
  line `(b) the District Judge may demand a like bond from any person to whom probate is granted.`
obj_root_law_sections_291_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_292:
  sectionId (34072)
  sectionNo (292)
  orderNo 293
  title `Assignment of administration-bond`
  content obj_root_law_sections_292_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_292_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=34072&sectionno=292&orderno=293&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_292_content:
  string
  line `The Court may, on application made by petition and on`
  line `being satisfied that the engagement of any such bond has not been kept, and upon such terms as to`
  line `security, or providing that the money received be paid into Court, or otherwise, as the Court may think fit,`
  line `assign the same to some person, his executors or administrators, who shall thereupon be entitled to sue on`
  line `the said bond in his or their own name or names as if the same had been originally given to him or them`
  line `instead of to the Judge of the Court, and shall be entitled to recover thereon, as trustees for all persons`
  line `interested, the full amount recoverable in respect of any breach thereof,`
obj_root_law_sections_292_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_293:
  sectionId (33802)
  sectionNo (293)
  orderNo 294
  title `Time for grant of probate and administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_293_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_293_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33802&sectionno=293&orderno=294&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_293_content:
  string
  line `No probate of a will shall be granted until`
  line `after the expiration of seven clear days, and no letters of administration shall be granted until after the`
  line `expiration of fourteen clear days, from the day of the testator or intestate's death.`
obj_root_law_sections_293_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_294:
  sectionId (33803)
  sectionNo (294)
  orderNo 295
  title `Filing of original wills of which probate or administration with will annexed granted.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_294_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_294_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33803&sectionno=294&orderno=295&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_294_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every District Judge, or District Delegate, shall file and preserve all original wills, of which probate or`
  line `letters of administration with the will annexed may be granted by him, among the records of his Court,`
  line `until some public registry for wills is established.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall make regulations for the preservation and inspection of the wills so`
  line filed.
obj_root_law_sections_294_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_295:
  sectionId (33804)
  sectionNo (295)
  orderNo 296
  title `Procedure in contentious cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_295_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_295_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33804&sectionno=295&orderno=296&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_295_content:
  string
  line `In any case before the District Judge in which there is`
  line `contention, the proceedings shall take, as nearly as may be, the form of a regular suit, according to the`
  line `provisions of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) in which the petitioner for probate or letters`
  line `of administration, as the case may be, shall be the plaintiff, and the person who has appeared to oppose`
  line `the grant shall be the defendant.`
obj_root_law_sections_295_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_296:
  sectionId (33805)
  sectionNo (296)
  orderNo 297
  title `Surrender of revoked probate or letters of administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_296_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_296_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33805&sectionno=296&orderno=297&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_296_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a grant of probate or`
  line `letters of administration is revoked or annulled under this Act, the person to whom the grant was made`
  line `shall forthwith deliver up the probate or letters to the Court which made the grant.`
  line
  line `(2) If such person willfully and without reasonable cause omits so to deliver up the probate or letters,`
  line `he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to three months, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_296_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_297:
  sectionId (33806)
  sectionNo (297)
  orderNo 298
  title `Payment to executor or administrator before probate or administration revoked.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_297_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_297_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33806&sectionno=297&orderno=298&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_297_content:
  string
  line `When a`
  line `grant of probate or letters of administration is revoked, all payments bona fide made to any executor or`
  line `administrator under such grant before the revocation thereof shall, notwithstanding such revocation, be a`
  line `legal discharge to the person making the same; and the executor or administrator who has acted under any`
  line `such revoked grant may retain and reimburse himself in respect of any payments made by him which the`
  line `person to whom probate or letters of administration may afterwards be granted might have lawfully made.`
obj_root_law_sections_297_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_298:
  sectionId (33807)
  sectionNo (298)
  orderNo 299
  title `Power to refuse letters of administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_298_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_298_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33807&sectionno=298&orderno=299&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_298_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything hereinbefore contained,`
  line `it shall, where the deceased' was a Muhammadan, Buddhist or exempted person, or a Hindu, Sikh or Jaina`
  line `to whom section 57 does not apply, be in the discretion of the Court to make an order refusing, for`
  line `reasons to be recorded by it in writing, to grant any application for letters of administration made lousier`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_298_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_299:
  sectionId (33808)
  sectionNo (299)
  orderNo 300
  title `Appeals from orders of District Judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_299_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_299_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33808&sectionno=299&orderno=300&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_299_content:
  string
  line `Every order made by a District Judge by virtue of the`
  line `powers hereby conferred upon him shall be subject to appeal to the High. Court in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), applicable to appeals.`
obj_root_law_sections_299_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_300:
  sectionId (33809)
  sectionNo (300)
  orderNo 301
  title `Concurrent jurisdiction of High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_300_content
  footnotes `1. The words "and the province of Burma" omitted by the A.O. 1937.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33809&sectionno=300&orderno=301&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_300_content:
  string
  line `(1) The High Court shall have concurrent`
  line `jurisdiction with the District Judge in the exercise of all the powers hereby conferred upon the District`
  line Judge.
  line
  line `(2) Except in cases to which section 57 applies, no High Court, in exercise of the concurrent`
  line `jurisdiction hereby conferred over any local area beyond the limits of the towns of Calcutta, Madras and`
  line `Bombay ^1*** shall, where the deceased is a Hindu, Muhammadan, Buddhist, Sikh or Jaina or an`
  line `exempted person, receive applications for probate or letters of administration until the State Government`
  line `has by a notification in the Official Gazette, authorised it so to do.`
obj_root_law_sections_301:
  sectionId (33810)
  sectionNo (301)
  orderNo 302
  title `Removal of executor or administrator and provision for successor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_301_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_301_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33810&sectionno=301&orderno=302&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_301_content:
  string
  line `The High Court may,`
  line `on application made to it, suspend, remove or discharge any private executor or administrator and provide`
  line `for the succession of another person to the office of any' such executor or administrator who may cease to`
  line `hold office, and the vesting in such successor of any property belonging to the estate.`
obj_root_law_sections_301_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_302:
  sectionId (33811)
  sectionNo (302)
  orderNo 303
  title `Directions to executor or administrator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_302_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_302_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33811&sectionno=302&orderno=303&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_302_content:
  string
  line `Where probate or letters of administration in`
  line `respect of any estate has or have been granted under this Act, the High Court may, on application made to`
  line `it, give to the executor or administrator any general or special directions in regard to the estate or in`
  line `regard to the administration thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_302_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_303:
  sectionId (33812)
  sectionNo (303)
  orderNo 304
  title `Executor of his own wrong.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_303_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_303_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33812&sectionno=303&orderno=304&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_303_content:
  string
  line `A person who intermeddles with the estate of the deceased or`
  line `does any other act which belongs to the office of executor, while there is no rightful executor or`
  line `administrator in existence, thereby makes himself an executor of his own wrong.`
  line
  line `Exceptions.--(1) Intermeddling with the goods of the deceased for the purpose of preserving them or`
  line `providing for his funeral or for the immediate necessities of his family or property, does not make an`
  line `executor of his own wrong.`
  line
  line `(2) Dealing in the ordinary course of business with goods of the deceased received from another does`
  line `not make an executor of his own wrong.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(i) A uses or gives away or sells some of the goods of the deceased, or takes them to satisfy his own debt or`
  line `legacy or receives payment of the debts of the deceased. He is an executor of his own wrong.`
  line
  line `(ii) A, having been appointed agent by the deceased in his lifetime to collect his debts and sell his goods,`
  line `continues to do so after he has become aware of his death. He is an executor of his own wrong in respect of acts`
  line `done after he has become aware of the death of the deceased.`
  line
  line `(iii) A sues as executor of the deceased, not being such. He is an executor of his own wrong.`
obj_root_law_sections_303_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_304:
  sectionId (33813)
  sectionNo (304)
  orderNo 305
  title `Liability of executor of his own wrong.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_304_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_304_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33813&sectionno=304&orderno=305&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_304_content:
  string
  line `When a person has so acted as to become an`
  line `executor of his own wrong, he is answerable to the rightful executor or administrator, or to any creditor or`
  line `legatee of the deceased, to the extent of the assets which may have come to his hands after deducting`
  line `payments made to the rightful executor or administrator, and payments made in due course of`
  line administration.
obj_root_law_sections_304_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_305:
  sectionId (33814)
  sectionNo (305)
  orderNo 306
  title `In respect of causes of action surviving deceased and debts due at death.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_305_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_305_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33814&sectionno=305&orderno=306&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_305_content:
  string
  line `An executor or`
  line `administrator has the same power to sue in respect of all causes of action that survive the deceased, and`
  line `may exercise the same power for the recovery of debts as the deceased had when living.`
obj_root_law_sections_305_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_306:
  sectionId (33815)
  sectionNo (306)
  orderNo 307
  title `Demands and rights of action of or against deceased survive to and against executor or administrator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_306_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_306_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33815&sectionno=306&orderno=307&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_306_content:
  string
  line `All demands whatsoever and all rights to prosecute or defend any action or special`
  line `proceeding existing in favour of or against a person at the time of his decease, survive to and against his`
  line `executors or administrators; except causes of action for defamation, assault, as defined in the Indian Penal`
  line `Code (45 of 1860), or other personal injuries not causing the death of the party; and except also cases`
  line `where, after the death of the party, the relief sought could not be enjoyed or granting it would be`
  line nugatory.
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(i) A collision takes place on a railway in consequence of some neglect or default of an official, and a passenger`
  line `is severely hurt, but not so as to cause death. He afterwards dies without having brought any action. action does not`
  line survive.
  line
  line `(ii) A sues for divorce. A dies. The cause of action does not survive to his representative.`
obj_root_law_sections_306_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_307:
  sectionId (33816)
  sectionNo (307)
  orderNo 308
  title `Power of executor or administrator to dispose of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_307_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_307_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33816&sectionno=307&orderno=308&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_307_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (2), and executor or administrator has power to dispose of the property of the deceased,`
  line `vested in him under section 211, either wholly or in part, in such manner as he may think fit.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(i) The deceased has made a specific bequest of part of his property. The executor, not having assented to the`
  line `bequest, sells the subject of it. The sale is valid.`
  line
  line `(ii) The executor in the exercise of his discretion mortgages a part of the immoveable estate of the deceased.`
  line `The mortgage is valid.`
  line
  line `(2) If the deceased was a Hindu, Muhammad an, Buddhist, Sikh or Jaina or an exempted person, the`
  line `general power conferred by sub-section (1) shall be subject to the following restrictions and conditions,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) The power of an executor to dispose of immovable property so vested in him is subject to any`
  line `restriction which may be imposed in this behalf by the Will appointing him, unless probate has been`
  line `granted to him and the Court which granted the probate permits him by an order in writing,`
  line `notwithstanding the restriction, to dispose of any immovable property specified in the order in a`
  line `manner permitted by the order.`
  line
  line `(ii) An administrator may not, without the previous permission of the Court by which the letters`
  line `of administration were granted,--`
  line
  line `(a) mortgage, charge or transfer by sale, gift, exchange or otherwise any immovable property`
  line `for the time being vested in him under section 211, or`
  line
  line `(b) lease any such property for a term exceeding five years.`
  line
  line `(iii) A disposal of property by an executor or administrator in contravention of clause (i) or clause`
  line `(ii), as the case may be, is voidable at the instance of any other person interested in the property.`
  line
  line `(3) Before any probate or letters of administration is or are granted in such a case, there shall be`
  line `endorsed thereon or annexed thereto a copy of sub-section (1) and clauses (i) and (iii) of`
  line `sub-section (2) or of sub-section (1) and clauses (ii) and (iii) of sub-section (2), as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) A probate or letters of administration shall not be rendered invalid by reason of the endorsement`
  line `or annexure required by sub-section (3) not having been made thereon or attached thereto, nor shall the`
  line `absence of such an endorsement or annexure authorise an executor or administrator to act otherwise than`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_307_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_308:
  sectionId (33817)
  sectionNo (308)
  orderNo 309
  title `General powers of administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_308_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_308_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33817&sectionno=308&orderno=309&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_308_content:
  string
  line `An executor or administrator may, in addition to, and not`
  line `in derogation of any other powers of expenditure lawfully exercisable by him, incur expenditure--`
  line
  line `(a) on such acts as may be necessary for the proper care or management of any property`
  line `belonging to any estate administered by him; and`
  line
  line `(b) with the sanction of the High Court, on such religious, charitable and other objects, and on`
  line `such improvements, as may be reasonable and proper in the case of such property.`
obj_root_law_sections_308_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_309:
  sectionId (33818)
  sectionNo (309)
  orderNo 310
  title `Commission or agency charges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_309_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_309_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33818&sectionno=309&orderno=310&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_309_content:
  string
  line `An executor or administrator shall not be entitled to receive`
  line `or retain any commission or agency charges at a higher rate than that for the time being fixed in respect of`
  line `the Administrator-General by or under the Administrator-Generals Act, 1913 (3 of 1913).`
obj_root_law_sections_309_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_310:
  sectionId (33819)
  sectionNo (310)
  orderNo 311
  title `Purchase by executor or administrator of deceased’s property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_310_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_310_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33819&sectionno=310&orderno=311&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_310_content:
  string
  line `If any executor or`
  line `administrator purchases, either directly or indirectly, any part of the property of the deceased, the sale is`
  line `voidable at the instance of any other person interested in the property sold.`
obj_root_law_sections_310_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_311:
  sectionId (33820)
  sectionNo (311)
  orderNo 312
  title `Powers of several executors or administrators exercisable by one.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_311_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_311_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33820&sectionno=311&orderno=312&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_311_content:
  string
  line `When there are several`
  line `executors or administrators, the powers of all may, in the absence of any direction to the contrary, be`
  line `exercised by any one of them who has proved the Will or taken out administration.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(i) One of several executors has power to release a debt due to the deceased.`
  line
  line `(ii) One has power to surrender a lease.`
  line
  line `(iii) One has power to sell the property of the deceased whether movable or immovable.`
  line
  line `(iv) One has power to assent to a legacy.`
  line
  line `(v) One has power to endorse a promissory note payable to the deceased.`
  line
  line `(vi) The Will appoints A, B, C and D to be executors, and directs that two of them shall be a quorum. No act can`
  line `be done by a single executor.`
obj_root_law_sections_311_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_312:
  sectionId (33821)
  sectionNo (312)
  orderNo 313
  title `Survival of powers on death of one of several executors or administrators.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_312_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_312_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33821&sectionno=312&orderno=313&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_312_content:
  string
  line `Upon the death`
  line `of one or more of several executors or administrators, in the absence of any direction to the contrary in`
  line `the will or grant of letters of administration, all the powers of the office become vested in the survivors or`
  line survivor.
obj_root_law_sections_312_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_313:
  sectionId (33822)
  sectionNo (313)
  orderNo 314
  title `Powers of administrator of effects unadministered.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_313_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_313_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33822&sectionno=313&orderno=314&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_313_content:
  string
  line `The administrator of effects`
  line `unadministered has, with respect to such effects, the same powers as the original executor or`
  line administrator.
obj_root_law_sections_313_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_314:
  sectionId (33823)
  sectionNo (314)
  orderNo 315
  title `Powers of administrator during minority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_314_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_314_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33823&sectionno=314&orderno=315&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_314_content:
  string
  line `An administrator during minority has all the`
  line `powers of an ordinary administrator:`
obj_root_law_sections_314_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_315:
  sectionId (33824)
  sectionNo (315)
  orderNo 316
  title `Powers of married executrix or administratrix.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_315_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_315_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33824&sectionno=315&orderno=316&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_315_content:
  string
  line `When a grant of probate or letters of`
  line `administration has been made to a married woman, she has all the powers of an ordinary executor or`
  line administrator.
obj_root_law_sections_315_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_316:
  sectionId (33825)
  sectionNo (316)
  orderNo 317
  title `As to deceased’s funeral.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_316_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_316_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33825&sectionno=316&orderno=317&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_316_content:
  string
  line `It is the duty of an executor to provide funds for the performance of`
  line `the necessary funeral ceremonies of the deceased in a manner suitable to his condition, if he has left`
  line `property sufficient for the purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_316_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_317:
  sectionId (33826)
  sectionNo (317)
  orderNo 318
  title `Inventory and account.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_317_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_317_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33826&sectionno=317&orderno=318&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_317_content:
  string
  line `(1) An executor or administrator shall, within six months from the`
  line `grant of probate or letters of administration, or within such further time as the Court which granted the`
  line `probate or letters may appoint, exhibit in that Court an inventory containing a full and true estimate of. all`
  line `the property in possession, and all the credits, and also all the debts owing by any person to which the`
  line `executor or administrator is entitled in that character; and shall in like manner, within one year from the`
  line `grant or within such further time as the said Court may appoint, exhibit an account of the estate, showing`
  line `the assets which have come to his hands and the manner in which they have been applied or disposed of.`
  line
  line `The High Court may prescribe the form in which an inventory or account under this section is to be`
  line exhibited.
  line
  line `If an executor or administrator, on being required by the Court to exhibit an inventory or account`
  line `under this section, intentionally omits to comply with the requisition, he shall be deemed to have`
  line `committed an offence under section 176 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `The exhibition of an intentionally false inventory or account under this section shall be deemed to be`
  line `an offence under section 193 of that Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_317_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_318:
  sectionId (33827)
  sectionNo (318)
  orderNo 319
  title `Inventory to include property in any part of India in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_318_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_318_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33827&sectionno=318&orderno=319&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_318_content:
  string
  line `in all cases where a`
  line `grant has been made of probate or letters of administration intended to have`
  line
  line `effect throughout ^1[India] ^2***, the executor or administrator shall include in the inventory of the`
  line `effects of the deceased all his moveable and immoveable property situate in 'India, and the value of such`
  line `property situate in each state shall be separately stated in such inventory, and the probate or letters of`
  line `administration shall be chargeable with a fee corresponding to the entire amount or value of the property`
  line `affected thereby wheresoever situate within ^1[India].`
obj_root_law_sections_318_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "the States".`
  line
  line `2. The words of "India" omitted by Act 48 of 1952, s. 3 and the Second Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_319:
  sectionId (33828)
  sectionNo (319)
  orderNo 320
  title `As to property of, and debts owing to, deceased.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_319_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_319_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33828&sectionno=319&orderno=320&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_319_content:
  string
  line `The executor or administrator shall collect,`
  line `with reasonable diligence, the property of the deceased and the debts that were due to him at the time of`
  line `his death.`
obj_root_law_sections_319_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_320:
  sectionId (33829)
  sectionNo (320)
  orderNo 321
  title `Expenses to be paid before all debts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_320_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_320_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33829&sectionno=320&orderno=321&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_320_content:
  string
  line `Funeral expenses to a reasonable amount, according to`
  line `the degree and quality of the deceased, and death-bed charges, including fees for medical attendance, and`
  line `board and lodging for one month previous to his death, shall be paid before all debts.`
obj_root_law_sections_320_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_321:
  sectionId (33830)
  sectionNo (321)
  orderNo 322
  title `Expenses to be paid next after such expenses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_321_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_321_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33830&sectionno=321&orderno=322&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_321_content:
  string
  line `The expenses of obtaining probate or letters of`
  line `administration, including the costs incurred for or in respect of any judicial proceedings that may be`
  line `necessary for administering the estate, shall be paid next after the funeral expenses and death-bed charges.`
obj_root_law_sections_321_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_322:
  sectionId (33831)
  sectionNo (322)
  orderNo 323
  title `Wages for certain services to be next paid, and then other debts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_322_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_322_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33831&sectionno=322&orderno=323&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_322_content:
  string
  line `Wages due for services`
  line `rendered to the deceased within three months next preceding his death by any labourer, artizan or`
  line `domestic servant shall next be paid, and then the other debts of the deceased according to their respective`
  line `priorities (if any).`
obj_root_law_sections_322_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_323:
  sectionId (33832)
  sectionNo (323)
  orderNo 324
  title `Save as aforesaid, all debts to be paid equally and rateably.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_323_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_323_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33832&sectionno=323&orderno=324&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_323_content:
  string
  line `Save as aforesaid, no creditor`
  line `shall have a right of priority over another; but the executor or administrator shall pay all such debts as he`
  line `knows of, including his own, equally and rateably as far as the assets of the deceased will extend.`
obj_root_law_sections_323_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_324:
  sectionId (33833)
  sectionNo (324)
  orderNo 325
  title `Application of moveable property to payment of debts where domicile not in India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_324_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule for "the States".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33833&sectionno=324&orderno=325&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_324_content:
  string
  line `(1) If`
  line `the domicile of the deceased was not in ^1[India], the application of his moveable property to the payment`
  line `of his debts is to be regulated by the law of ^1[India].`
  line
  line `(2) No creditor who has received payment of a part of his debt by virtue of sub-section (1) shall be`
  line `entitled to share in the proceeds of the immoveable estate of the deceased unless he brings such payment`
  line `into account for the benefit of the other creditors.`
  line
  line `(3) This section shall not apply where the deceased was a Hindu, Muhammadan, Buddhist, Sikh or`
  line `Jaina or an exempted person.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `A dies, having his domicile in a country where instruments under seal have priority over instruments not under`
  line `seal leaving moveable property to the value of 5,000 rupees, and immoveable property to the value of 10,000 rupees,`
  line `debts on instruments under seal to the amount of 10,000 rupees, and debts on instruments not under seal to the same`
  line `mount. The creditors holding instruments under seal received half of their debts out of the proceeds of the moveable`
  line `estate. The proceeds of the immoveable estate are to be applied in payment of the debts on instruments not under`
  line `seal until one-half of such debts have been discharged. This will leave 5,000 rupees which are to be distributed`
  line `rateably amongst all the creditors without distinction, in proportion to the amount which may remain due to them.`
obj_root_law_sections_325:
  sectionId (33834)
  sectionNo (325)
  orderNo 326
  title `Debts to be paid before legacies.`
  content `Debts of every description must be paid before any legacy.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_325_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33834&sectionno=325&orderno=326&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_325_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_326:
  sectionId (33835)
  sectionNo (326)
  orderNo 327
  title `Executor or administrator not bound to pay legacies without indemnity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_326_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_326_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33835&sectionno=326&orderno=327&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_326_content:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_326_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_327:
  sectionId (33836)
  sectionNo (327)
  orderNo 328
  title `Abatement of general legacies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_327_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_327_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33836&sectionno=327&orderno=328&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_327_content:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_327_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_328:
  sectionId (33837)
  sectionNo (328)
  orderNo 329
  title `Non-abatement of specific legacy when assets sufficient to pay debts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_328_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_328_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33837&sectionno=328&orderno=329&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_328_content:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_328_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_329:
  sectionId (33838)
  sectionNo (329)
  orderNo 330
  title `Right under demonstrative legacy when assets sufficient to pay debts and necessary expenses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_329_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_329_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33838&sectionno=329&orderno=330&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_329_content:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_329_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_330:
  sectionId (33839)
  sectionNo (330)
  orderNo 331
  title `Rateable abatement of specific legacies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_330_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_330_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33839&sectionno=330&orderno=331&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_330_content:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_330_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_331:
  sectionId (33840)
  sectionNo (331)
  orderNo 332
  title `Legacies treated as general for purpose of abatement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_331_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_331_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33840&sectionno=331&orderno=332&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_331_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of abatement, a`
  line `legacy for life, a sum appropriated by the will to produce an annuity, and the value of an annuity when no`
  line `sum has been appropriated to produce it, shall be treated as general legacies.`
obj_root_law_sections_331_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_332:
  sectionId (33841)
  sectionNo (332)
  orderNo 333
  title `Assent necessary to complete legatee’s title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_332_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_332_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33841&sectionno=332&orderno=333&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_332_content:
  string
  line `The assent of the executor or administrator is`
  line `necessary to complete a legatee's title to his legacy.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(i) A by his will bequeaths to B his Government paper which is in deposit with the Imperial Bank of India. The`
  line `Bank has no authority to deliver the securities, nor B a right to take possession of them, without the assent of the`
  line executor.
  line
  line `(ii) A by- his will has bequeathed to C his house in Calcutta in the tenancy of B. C is not entitled to receive the`
  line `rents without the assent of the executor or administrator.`
obj_root_law_sections_332_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_333:
  sectionId (33842)
  sectionNo (333)
  orderNo 334
  title `Effect of executor’s assent to specific legacy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_333_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_333_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33842&sectionno=333&orderno=334&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_333_content:
  string
  line `(1) The assent of the executor or administrator`
  line `to a specific bequest shall be sufficient tb divest his interest as executor or administrator therein, and to`
  line `transfer the subject of the bequest of the legatee, unless the nature or the circumstances of the property`
  line `require that it shall be transferred in a particular way.`
  line
  line `(2) This assent may be verbal, and it may be either express or implied from the conduct of the`
  line `executor or administrator.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(i) A horse is bequeathed. The executor requests the legatee to dispose of it, or a third party proposes to`
  line `purchase the horse from the executor, and he directs him to apply to the legatee. Assent to the legacy is implied.`
  line
  line `(ii) The interest of a fund is directed by the will to be applied for the maintenance of the legatee during his`
  line `minority. The executor commences so to apply it. This is an assent to the whole of the bequest.`
  line
  line `(iii) A bequest is made of a fund to A and after him to B. The executor pays the interest of the fund to A. This is`
  line `an implied assent to the bequest to B.`
  line
  line `(iv) Executors die after paying all the debts of the testator, but before satisfaction of specific legacies. Assent to`
  line `the legacies may be presumed.`
  line
  line `(v) A person to whom a specific article has been bequeathed takes possession of it and retains it without any`
  line `objection on the part of the executor. His assent may be presumed.`
obj_root_law_sections_333_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_334:
  sectionId (33843)
  sectionNo (334)
  orderNo 335
  title `Conditional assent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_334_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_334_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33843&sectionno=334&orderno=335&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_334_content:
  string
  line `The assent of an executor or administrator to a legacy may be conditional,`
  line `and if the condition is one which he has a right to enforce, and it is not performed, there is no assent.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(i) A bequeaths to B his lands of Sultanpur, which at the date of the will, and at the death of A, were subject to a`
  line `mortgage for 10,000 rupees. The executor assents to the bequest, on condition that B shall within a limited time pay`
  line `the amount due on the mortgage at the testator's death. The amount is not paid. There is no assent.`
  line
  line `(ii) The executor assents to a bequest on condition that the legatee shall pay him a sum of money. The payment`
  line `is not made. The assent is nevertheless valid.`
obj_root_law_sections_334_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_335:
  sectionId (33844)
  sectionNo (335)
  orderNo 336
  title `Assent of executor to his own legacy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_335_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_335_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33844&sectionno=335&orderno=336&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_335_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the executor or administrator is a legatee, his`
  line `assent to his own legacy is necessary to complete his title to it, in the same way as it is required when the`
  line `bequest is to another person, and his assent may, in like manner, be expressed or implied.`
  line
  line `(2) Assent shall be implied if in his manner of administering the property he does any act which is`
  line `referable to his character of legatee and is not referable to his character of executor or administrator.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `An executor takes the rent of a house or the interest of Government securities bequeathed to him and applied it`
  line `to his own use. This is assent.`
obj_root_law_sections_335_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_336:
  sectionId (33845)
  sectionNo (336)
  orderNo 337
  title `Effect of executor’s assent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_336_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_336_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33845&sectionno=336&orderno=337&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_336_content:
  string
  line `The assent of the executor or administrator to a legacy gives`
  line `effect to it from the death of the testator.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(i) A legatee sells his legacy before it is assented to by the executor. The executor's subsequent assent operates`
  line `for the benefit of the purchaser and completes his title to the legacy.`
  line
  line `(ii) A bequeaths 1,000 rupees to B with interest from his death. The executor does not assent to his legacy until`
  line `the expiration of a year from A's death. B is entitled to interest from the death of A.`
obj_root_law_sections_336_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_337:
  sectionId (33846)
  sectionNo (337)
  orderNo 338
  title `Executor when to deliver legacies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_337_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_337_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33846&sectionno=337&orderno=338&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_337_content:
  string
  line `An executor or administrator is not bound to pay or`
  line `deliver any legacy until the expiration of one year from the testator's death.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `A by his will directs his legacies to be paid within six months after his death. The executor is not bound to pay`
  line `them before the expiration of a year.`
obj_root_law_sections_337_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_338:
  sectionId (33847)
  sectionNo (338)
  orderNo 339
  title `Commencement of annuity when no time fixed by will.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_338_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_338_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33847&sectionno=338&orderno=339&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_338_content:
  string
  line `Where an annuity is given by a will`
  line `and no time is fixed for its commencement, it shall commence from the testator's death, and the first`
  line `payment shall be made at the expiration of a year next after that event.`
obj_root_law_sections_338_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_339:
  sectionId (33848)
  sectionNo (339)
  orderNo 340
  title `When annuity, to be paid quarterly or monthly, first falls due.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_339_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_339_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33848&sectionno=339&orderno=340&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_339_content:
  string
  line `Where there is a direction`
  line `that the annuity shall be paid quarterly or monthly, the first payment shall be due at the end of the first`
  line `quarter or first month, as the case may be, after the testator's death; and shall, if the executor or`
  line `administrator thinks fit, be paid when due, but the executor or administrator shall not be bound to pay it`
  line `till the end of the year.`
obj_root_law_sections_339_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_340:
  sectionId (33849)
  sectionNo (340)
  orderNo 341
  title `Dates of successive payments when first payment directed to be made within a given time or on day certain: death of annuitant before date of payment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_340_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_340_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33849&sectionno=340&orderno=341&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_340_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where there is a direction that the`
  line `first payment of an annuity shall be made within one month or any other division of time from the death`
  line `of the testator, or on a day certain, the successive payments are to be made on the anniversary of the`
  line `earliest day on which the will authorises the first payment to be made.`
  line
  line `(2) If the annuitant dies in the interval between the times of payment, an apportioned share of the`
  line `annuity shall be paid to his representative.`
obj_root_law_sections_340_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_341:
  sectionId (33850)
  sectionNo (341)
  orderNo 342
  title `Investment of sum bequeathed, where legacy, not specific, given for life.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_341_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_341_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33850&sectionno=341&orderno=342&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_341_content:
  string
  line `Where a legacy,`
  line `not being a specific legacy, is given for life, the sum bequeathed shall at the end of the year he invested in`
  line `such securities as the High Court may by any general rule authorise or direct, and the proceeds thereof`
  line `shall be paid to the legatee as the same shall accrue due.`
obj_root_law_sections_341_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_342:
  sectionId (33851)
  sectionNo (342)
  orderNo 343
  title `Investment of general legacy, to be paid at future time: disposal of intermediate, interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_342_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_342_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33851&sectionno=342&orderno=343&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_342_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a general legacy is given to be paid at a future time, the executor or administrator shall invest a`
  line `sum sufficient to meet it in securities of the kind mentioned in section 341.`
  line
  line `(2) The intermediate interest shall form part of the residue of the testator's estate.`
obj_root_law_sections_342_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_343:
  sectionId (33852)
  sectionNo (343)
  orderNo 344
  title `Procedure when no fund charged with, or appropriated to, annuity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_343_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_343_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33852&sectionno=343&orderno=344&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_343_content:
  string
  line `Where an annuity is`
  line `given and no fund is charged with its payment or appropriated by the will to answer it, a Government`
  line `annuity of the specified amount shall be purchased, or, if no such annuity can be obtained, then a sum`
  line `sufficient to produce the annuity shall be invested for that purpose in securities of the kind mentioned in`
  line `section 341.`
obj_root_law_sections_343_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_344:
  sectionId (33853)
  sectionNo (344)
  orderNo 345
  title `Transfer to residuary legatee of contingent bequest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_344_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_344_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33853&sectionno=344&orderno=345&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_344_content:
  string
  line `Where a bequest is contingent, the`
  line `executor or administrator is not bound to invest the amount of the legacy, but may transfer the whole`
  line `residue of the estate to the residuary legatee, if any, on his giving sufficient security for the payment of`
  line `the legacy, if it shall become due.`
obj_root_law_sections_344_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_345:
  sectionId (33854)
  sectionNo (345)
  orderNo 346
  title `Investment of residue bequeathed for life, without direction to invest in particular securities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_345_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_345_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33854&sectionno=345&orderno=346&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_345_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the testator has bequeathed the residue of his estate to a person for life without`
  line `any direction to invest it in any particular securities, so much thereof as is not at the time of the testator's`
  line `decease invested in securities of the kind mentioned in section 341 shall be converted into money and`
  line `invested in such securities.`
  line
  line `(2) This section shall not apply if the deceased was a Hindu, Muhammadan, Buddhist, Sikh or Jaina`
  line `or an exempted person.`
obj_root_law_sections_345_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_346:
  sectionId (33855)
  sectionNo (346)
  orderNo 347
  title `Investment of residue bequeathed for life, with direction to invest in specified securities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_346_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_346_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33855&sectionno=346&orderno=347&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_346_content:
  string
  line `When the testator has bequeathed the residue of his estate of a person for life with a direction that it shall`
  line `be invested in certain specified securities, so much of the estate as is not at the time of his death invested`
  line `in securities of the specified kind shall be converted into money and invested in such securities.`
obj_root_law_sections_346_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_347:
  sectionId (33856)
  sectionNo (347)
  orderNo 348
  title `Time and manner of conversion and investment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_347_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_347_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33856&sectionno=347&orderno=348&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_347_content:
  string
  line `Such conversion and investment as are`
  line `contemplated by sections 345 and 346 shall be made at such times and in such manner as the executor or`
  line `administrator thinks fit; and, until such conversion and investment are completed, the person who would`
  line `be for the time being entitled to the income of the fund when so invested shall receive interest at the rate`
  line `of 4 per cent. per annum upon the market-value (to be computed as at the date of the testator's death) of`
  line `such part of the fund as has not been so invested:`
  line
  line `Provided that the rate of interest prior to completion of investment shall be six per cent. per annum`
  line `when the testator was a Hindu, Muhammadan, Buddhist, Sikh or Jaina or an exempted person`
obj_root_law_sections_347_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_348:
  sectionId (33857)
  sectionNo (348)
  orderNo 349
  title `Procedure where minor entitled to immediate payment or possession of bequest, and no direction to pay to person on his behalf.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_348_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_348_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33857&sectionno=348&orderno=349&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_348_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, by the terms of a bequest, the legatee is entitled to`
  line `the immediate payment or possession of the money or thing bequeathed, but is a minor, and there is no`
  line `direction in the will to pay it to any person on his behalf, the executor or administrator shall pay or deliver`
  line `the same into the Court of the District Judge, by whom or by whose District Delegate the probate was, or`
  line `letters of administration with the will annexed were, granted to the account of the legatee, unless the`
  line `legatee is a ward of the Court of Wards.`
  line
  line `(2) If the legatee is a ward of the Court of Wards, the legacy shall be paid to the Court of Wards to his`
  line account.
  line
  line `(3) Such payment into the Court of the District Judge, or to the Court of Wards, as the case may be,`
  line `shall be a sufficient discharge for the money so paid.`
  line
  line `(4) Money when paid in under this section shall be invested in the purchase of Government securities,`
  line `which, with the interest thereon, shall be transferred or paid to the person entitled thereto, or otherwise`
  line `applied for his benefit, as the Judge or the Court of Wards, as the case may be, may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_348_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_349:
  sectionId (33858)
  sectionNo (349)
  orderNo 350
  title `Legatee’s title to produce of specific legacy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_349_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_349_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33858&sectionno=349&orderno=350&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_349_content:
  string
  line `The legatee of a specific legacy is entitled to the`
  line `clear produce thereof. if any, from the testator's death.`
  line
  line `Exception.-- A specific bequest, contingent in its terms, does not comprise the produce of the legacy`
  line `between the death of the testator and the vesting of the legacy. The clear produce of it forms part of the`
  line `residue of the testator's estate.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(i) A bequeaths his flock of sheep to B. Between the death of A and delivery by his executor the sheep are shorn`
  line `or some of the ewes produce lambs. The wool and lambs are the property of B.`
  line
  line `(ii) A bequeaths his Government securities to B, but postpones the delivery of them till the death of C. The`
  line `interest which falls due between the death of A and the death of C belongs to B, and must, unless he is a minor, be`
  line `paid to him as it is received.`
  line
  line `(iii) The testator bequeaths all his four per cent. Government promissory notes to A when he shall complete the`
  line `age of 18. A, if he completes that age, is entitled to receive the notes, but the interest which accrues in respect of`
  line `them between the testator's death and As completing 18, form part of the residue.`
obj_root_law_sections_349_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_350:
  sectionId (33859)
  sectionNo (350)
  orderNo 351
  title `Residuary legatee’s title to produce of residuary fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_350_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_350_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33859&sectionno=350&orderno=351&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_350_content:
  string
  line `The legatee under a general`
  line `residuary bequest is entitled to the produce of the residuary fund from the testator's death.`
  line
  line `Exception.-- A general residuary bequest contingent in its terms does not comprise the income which`
  line `may accrue upon the fund bequeathed between the death of the testator and the vesting of the legacy.`
  line `Such income goes as undisposed of.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(i) The testator bequeaths the residue of his property to A, a minor, to be paid to him when he shall complete the`
  line `age of 18. The income from the testator's death belongs to A.`
  line
  line `(ii) The testator bequeaths the residue of his property to A when he shall complete the age of 18. A, if he`
  line `completes that age, is entitled to receive the residue. The income which has accrued in respect of it since the`
  line `testator's death goes as undisposed of.`
obj_root_law_sections_350_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_351:
  sectionId (33860)
  sectionNo (351)
  orderNo 352
  title `Interest when no time fixed for payment of general legacy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_351_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_351_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33860&sectionno=351&orderno=352&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_351_content:
  string
  line `Where no time has been fixed`
  line `for the payment of a general legacy, interest begins to run from expiration of one year from the testator's`
  line death.
  line
  line `Exception.-- (1) Where the legacy is bequeathed in satisfaction of a debt, interest runs from the death`
  line `of the testator.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the testator was a parent or a more remote ancestor of the legatee, or has put himself in the`
  line `place of a parent of the legatee, the legacy shall bear interest from the death of the testator.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a sum is bequeathed to a minor with a direction to pay for his maintenance out of it,`
  line `interest is payable from the death of the testator.`
obj_root_law_sections_351_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_352:
  sectionId (33861)
  sectionNo (352)
  orderNo 353
  title `Interest when time fixed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_352_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_352_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33861&sectionno=352&orderno=353&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_352_content:
  string
  line `Where a time has been fixed for the payment of a general legacy,`
  line `interest begins to run from the time so fixed. The interest up to such time forms part of the residue of the`
  line `testator's estate.`
  line
  line `Exception.-- Where the testator was a parent or a more remote ancestor of the legatee, or has put`
  line `himself in the place of a parent of the legatee and the legatee is a minor, the legacy shall bear interest`
  line `from the death of the testator, unless a specific sum is given by the will for maintenance, or unless the`
  line `will contains a direction to the contrary.`
obj_root_law_sections_352_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_353:
  sectionId (33862)
  sectionNo (353)
  orderNo 354
  title `Rate of interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_353_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_353_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33862&sectionno=353&orderno=354&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_353_content:
  string
  line `The rate of interest shall be four per cent. per annum in all cases except when`
  line `the testator was a Hindu, Muhammadan, Buddhist, Sikh or Jaina or an exempted person, in which case it`
  line `shall be six per cent. per annum.`
obj_root_law_sections_353_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_354:
  sectionId (33863)
  sectionNo (354)
  orderNo 355
  title `No interest on arrears of annuity within first year after testator’s death.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_354_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_354_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33863&sectionno=354&orderno=355&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_354_content:
  string
  line `No interest is`
  line `payable on the arrears of an annuity within the first year from the death of the testator, although a period`
  line `earlier than the expiration of that year may have been fixed by will for making the first payment of the`
  line annuity.
obj_root_law_sections_354_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_355:
  sectionId (33864)
  sectionNo (355)
  orderNo 356
  title `Interest on sum to be invested produce annuity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_355_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_355_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33864&sectionno=355&orderno=356&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_355_content:
  string
  line `Where a sum of money is directed to be`
  line `invested to produce an annuity, interest is payable on it from the death of the testator.`
obj_root_law_sections_355_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_356:
  sectionId (33865)
  sectionNo (356)
  orderNo 357
  title `Refund of legacy paid under Court’s orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_356_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_356_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33865&sectionno=356&orderno=357&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_356_content:
  string
  line `When an executor or administrator has paid a`
  line `legacy under the order of a Court, he is entitled to call upon the legatee to refund in the event of the assets`
  line `proving insufficient to pay all the legacies.`
obj_root_law_sections_356_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_357:
  sectionId (33866)
  sectionNo (357)
  orderNo 358
  title `No refund if paid voluntarily.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_357_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_357_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33866&sectionno=357&orderno=358&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_357_content:
  string
  line `When an executor or administrator has voluntarily paid a`
  line `legacy, he cannot call upon a legatee to refund in the event of the assets proving insufficient to pay all the`
  line legacies.
obj_root_law_sections_357_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_358:
  sectionId (33867)
  sectionNo (358)
  orderNo 359
  title `Refund when legacy has become due on performance of condition within further time allowed under section 137.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_358_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_358_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33867&sectionno=358&orderno=359&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_358_content:
  string
  line `When the time prescribed by the will for the performance of a condition`
  line `has elapsed, without the condition having been performed, and the executor or administrator has`
  line `thereupon, without fraud, distributed the assets; in such case, if further time has been allowed under`
  line `section 137 for the performance of the condition, and the condition has been performed accordingly, the`
  line `legacy cannot be claimed from the executor or administrator, but those to whom he has paid it are liable`
  line `to refund the amount.`
obj_root_law_sections_358_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_359:
  sectionId (33868)
  sectionNo (359)
  orderNo 360
  title `When each legatee compellable to refund in proportion.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_359_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_359_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33868&sectionno=359&orderno=360&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_359_content:
  string
  line `When the executor or`
  line `administrator has paid away the assets in legacies, and he is afterwards obliged to discharge a debt of`
  line `which he had no previous notice, he is entitled to call upon each legatee to refund in proportion.`
obj_root_law_sections_359_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_360:
  sectionId (33869)
  sectionNo (360)
  orderNo 361
  title `Distribution of assets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_360_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_360_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33869&sectionno=360&orderno=361&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_360_content:
  string
  line `Where an executor or administrator has given such notices as the High`
  line `Court may, by any general rule, prescribe or, if no such rule has been made, as the High Court would give`
  line `in an administration-suit, for creditors and others to sent in to him their claims against the state of the`
  line `deceased, he shall, at the expiration of the time therein named for sending in claims, be at liberty to`
  line `distribute the assets, or any part thereof, in discharge of such lawful claims as he knows of, and shall not`
  line `be liable for the assets so distributed to any person of whose claim he shall not have had notice at the time`
  line `of such distribution:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing herein contained shall prejudice the right of any creditor or claimant to follow`
  line `the assets, or any part thereof, in the hands of the persons who may have received the same respectively.`
obj_root_law_sections_360_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_361:
  sectionId (33870)
  sectionNo (361)
  orderNo 362
  title `Creditor may call upon legatee to refund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_361_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_361_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33870&sectionno=361&orderno=362&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_361_content:
  string
  line `A creditor who has not received payment of his`
  line `debt may call upon a legatee who has received paymeni of his legacy to refund, whether the assets of the`
  line `testator's estate were or were not sufficient at the time of his death to pay both debts and legacies; and`
  line `whether the payment of the legacy by the executor or administrator was voluntary or not.`
obj_root_law_sections_361_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_362:
  sectionId (33871)
  sectionNo (362)
  orderNo 363
  title `When legatee, not satisfied or compelled to refund under section 361, cannot oblige one paid in full to refund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_362_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_362_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33871&sectionno=362&orderno=363&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_362_content:
  string
  line `If the assets were sufficient to satisfy all the legacies at the time of the testator's`
  line `death, a legatee who has not received payment of his legacy, or who has been compelled to refund under`
  line `section 361, cannot oblige one who has received payment in full to refund, whether the legacy were paid`
  line `to him with or without suit, although the assets have subsequently become deficient by the wasting of the`
  line executor.
obj_root_law_sections_362_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_363:
  sectionId (33872)
  sectionNo (363)
  orderNo 364
  title `When unsatisfied legatee must first proceed against executor, if solvent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_363_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_363_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33872&sectionno=363&orderno=364&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_363_content:
  string
  line `If the assets were`
  line `not sufficient to satisfy all the legacies at the time of the testator's death, a legatee who has not received`
  line `payment of his legacy must, before he can call on a satisfied legatee to refund, first proceed against the`
  line `executor or administrator if he is solvent; but if the executor or administrator is insolvent or not liable to`
  line `pay, the unsatisfied legatee can oblige each satisfied legatee to refund in proportion.`
obj_root_law_sections_363_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_364:
  sectionId (33873)
  sectionNo (364)
  orderNo 365
  title `Limit to refunding of one legatee to another.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_364_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_364_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33873&sectionno=364&orderno=365&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_364_content:
  string
  line `The refunding of one legatee to another shall`
  line `not exceed the sum by which the satisfied legacy ought to have been reduced if the estate had been`
  line `properly administered.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `A has bequeathed 240 rupees, to B, 480 rupees to C, and 720 rupees to D. The assets are only 1,200 rupees and,`
  line `if properly administered, would give 200 rupees to B, 400 rupees to C and 600 rupees to D. C and D have been paid`
  line `their legacies in full leaving nothing to B. B can oblige C to refund 80 rupees, and D to refund 120 rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_364_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_365:
  sectionId (33874)
  sectionNo (365)
  orderNo 366
  title `Refunding to be without interest.`
  content `The refunding shall in all cases be without interest.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_365_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33874&sectionno=365&orderno=366&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_365_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_366:
  sectionId (33875)
  sectionNo (366)
  orderNo 367
  title `Residue after usual payments to be paid to residuary legatee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_366_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_366_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33875&sectionno=366&orderno=367&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_366_content:
  string
  line `The surplus or residue of the`
  line `deceased's property, after payment of debts and legacies, shall be paid to the residuary legatee when any`
  line `has been appointed by the will.`
obj_root_law_sections_366_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_367:
  sectionId (33876)
  sectionNo (367)
  orderNo 368
  title `Transfer of assets from India to executor or administrator in country of domicile for distribution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_367_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "the States".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33876&sectionno=367&orderno=368&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_367_content:
  string
  line `Where a person not having his domicile in ^1[India] has died leaving assets both in if`
  line `^1[India] and in the country in which he had his domicile at the time of his death, and there has been a`
  line `grant of probate or letters of administration in ^1[India] with respect to the assets there a grant of`
  line `administration in the country of domicile with respect to the assets in that country, the executor or`
  line `administrator, as the case may be, in ^1[India], after having given such notices as are mentioned in section`
  line `360, and after having discharged, at the expiration of the time therein named, such lawful claims as he`
  line `knows of, may, instead of himself distributing any surplus or residue of the deceaseds property to`
  line `persons residing out of ^1[India] who are entitled thereto, transfer, with the consent of the executor or`
  line `administrator, as the case may be, in the country of domicile, the surplus or residue to him for distribution`
  line `to those persons.`
obj_root_law_sections_368:
  sectionId (33877)
  sectionNo (368)
  orderNo 369
  title `Liability of executor or administrator for devastation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_368_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_368_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33877&sectionno=368&orderno=369&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_368_content:
  string
  line `When an executor or administrator`
  line `misapplies the estate of the deceased, or subjects it to loss or damage, he is liable to make good the loss or`
  line `damage so occasioned.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(i) The executor pays out of the estate an unfounded claim. He is liable to make good the loss.`
  line
  line `(ii) The deceased had a valuable lease renewable by notice which the executor neglects to give at the proper`
  line `time. The executor is liable to make good the loss.`
  line
  line `(iii) The deceased had a lease of less value than the rent payable for it, but terminable on notice at a particular`
  line `time. The executor neglects to give the notice. He is liable to make good the loss.`
obj_root_law_sections_368_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_369:
  sectionId (33878)
  sectionNo (369)
  orderNo 370
  title `Liability of executor or administrator for neglect to get any part of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_369_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_369_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33878&sectionno=369&orderno=370&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_369_content:
  string
  line `When an`
  line `executor or administrator occasions a loss to the estate by neglecting to get in any part of the property of`
  line `the deceased, he is liable to make good the amount.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(i) The executor absolutely releases a debt due to the deceased from a solvent person, or compounds with a`
  line `debtor who is able to pay in full. The executor is liable to make good the amount.`
  line
  line `(ii) The executor neglects to sue for a debt till the debtor is able to plead that the claim is barred by limitation`
  line `and the debt is thereby lost to the estate. The executor is liable to make good the amount.`
obj_root_law_sections_369_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_370:
  sectionId (33879)
  sectionNo (370)
  orderNo 371
  title `Restriction on grant of certificates under this part.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_370_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_370_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33879&sectionno=370&orderno=371&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_370_content:
  string
  line `(1) A succession certificate (hereinafter`
  line `in this Part referred to as a certificate) shall not be granted under this Part with respect to any debt or`
  line `security to which a right is required by section 212 or section 213 to be established by letters of`
  line `administration or probate:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall be deemed to prevent the grant of a certificate to`
  line `any person claiming to be entitled to the effects of a deceased Indian Christian, or to any part thereof,`
  line `with respect to any debt or security, by reason that a right thereto can be established by letters of`
  line `administration under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this Part, "security" means--`
  line
  line `(a) any promissory note, debenture, stock or other security of the Central Government or of a`
  line `State Government;`
  line
  line `(b) any bond, debenture, or annuity charged by Act of Parliament ^1[of the United Kingdom] on`
  line `the revenues of India;`
  line
  line `(c) any stock or debenture of, or share in, a company or other incorporated institution;`
  line
  line `(d) any debenture or other security for money issued by, or on behalf of, a local authority;`
  line
  line `(e) any other security which the ^2[State Government] may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `declare to be a security for the purposes of this Part.`
obj_root_law_sections_370_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by the A. O. 1950.`
  line
  line `2. The words "G.G. in C" have been successively amended by the A.O. 1937 and the A.O. 1950 to read as above.`
obj_root_law_sections_371:
  sectionId (33880)
  sectionNo (371)
  orderNo 372
  title `Court having jurisdiction to grant certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_371_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_371_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33880&sectionno=371&orderno=372&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_371_content:
  string
  line `The District Judge within whose jurisdiction`
  line `the deceased ordinarily resided at the time of his death, or, if at that time he had no fixed place of`
  line `residence, the District Judge, within whose jurisdiction any part of the property of the deceased may be`
  line `found, may grant a certificate under this Part.`
obj_root_law_sections_371_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_372:
  sectionId (33881)
  sectionNo (372)
  orderNo 373
  title `Application for certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_372_content
  footnotes `1. Added by Act 14 of 1928, s. 2.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33881&sectionno=372&orderno=373&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_372_content:
  string
  line `(1) Application for such a certificate shall be made to the District`
  line `Judge by a petition signed and verified by or on behalf of the applicant in the manner prescribed by the`
  line `Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) for the signing and verification of a plaint by or on behalf of a`
  line `plaintiff, and setting forth the following particulars, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the time of the death of the deceased;`
  line
  line `(b) the ordinary residence of the deceased at the time of his death and, if such residence was not`
  line `within the local limits of the jurisdiction of the Judge to whom the application is made, then the`
  line `property of the deceased within those limits;`
  line
  line `(c) the family or other near relatives of the deceased and their respective residences;`
  line
  line `(d) the right in which the petitioner claims;`
  line
  line `(e) the absence of any impediment under section 370 or under any other provision of this Act or`
  line `any other enactment, to the grant of the certificate or to the validity thereof if it were granted; and`
  line
  line `(f) the debts and securities in respect of which the certificate is applied for.`
  line
  line `(2) If the petition contains any averment which the person verifying it knows or believes to be false,`
  line `or does not believe to be true, that person shall be deemed to have committed an offence under section`
  line `198 of the Indian Penal Code, 1860 (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `^1[(3) Application for such a certificate may be made in respect of any debt or debts due to the`
  line `deceased creditor or in respect of portions thereof.]`
obj_root_law_sections_373:
  sectionId (33882)
  sectionNo (373)
  orderNo 374
  title `Procedure on application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_373_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_373_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33882&sectionno=373&orderno=374&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_373_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the District Judge is satisfied that there is ground for`
  line `entertaining the application, he shall fix a day for the hearing thereof and cause notice of the application`
  line `and of the day fixed for the hearing--`
  line
  line `(a) to be served on any person to whom, in the opinion of the Judge, special notice of the`
  line `application should be given, and`
  line
  line `(b) to be posted on some conspicuous part of the court-house and published in such other manner,`
  line `if any, as the Judge, subject to any rules made by the High Court in this behalf, thinks fit,`
  line
  line `and upon the day fixed, or as soon thereafter as may be practicable, shall proceed to decide in a summary`
  line `manner the right to the certificate.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Judge decides the right thereto to belong to the applicant, the Judge shall make an order`
  line `for the grant of the certificate to him.`
  line
  line `(3) If the Judge cannot decide the right to the certificate without determining questions of law or fact`
  line `which seem to be too intricate and difficult for determination in a summary proceeding, he may`
  line `nevertheless grant a certificate to the applicant if he appears to be the person having prima facie the best`
  line `title thereto.`
  line
  line `(4) When there are more applicants than one for a certificate, and it appears to the Judge that more`
  line `than one of such applicants are interested in the estate of the deceased, the Judge may, in deciding to`
  line `whom the certificate is to be granted, have regard to the extent of interest and the fitness in other respects`
  line `of the applicants.`
obj_root_law_sections_373_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_374:
  sectionId (33883)
  sectionNo (374)
  orderNo 375
  title `Contents of certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_374_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_374_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33883&sectionno=374&orderno=375&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_374_content:
  string
  line `When the District Judge grants a certificate, he shall therein specify`
  line `the debts and securities set forth in the application for the certificate, and may thereby empower the`
  line `person to whom the certificate is granted--`
  line
  line `(a) to receive interest or dividends on, or`
  line
  line `(b) to negotiate or transfer, or`
  line
  line `(c) both to receive interest or dividends on, and to negotiate or transfer, the securities or any of`
  line them.
obj_root_law_sections_374_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_375:
  sectionId (33884)
  sectionNo (375)
  orderNo 376
  title `Requisition of security from grantee of certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_375_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_375_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33884&sectionno=375&orderno=376&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_375_content:
  string
  line `(1) The District Judge shall in any case`
  line `in which he proposes to proceed under sub-section (3) or sub-section (4) of section 373, and may, in any`
  line `other case, require, as a condition precedent to the granting of a certificate, that the person to whom he`
  line `proposes to make the grant shall give to the Judge a bond with one or more surety or sureties, or other`
  line `sufficient security, for rendering an account of debts and securities received by him and for indemnity of`
  line `persons who may be entitled to the whole or any part of those debts and securities.`
  line
  line `(2) The Judge may, on application made by petitioner and on cause shown to his satisfaction, and`
  line `upon such terms as to security, or providing that the money received be paid into Court, or otherwise, as`
  line `he thinks fit, assign the bond or other security to some proper person, and that person shall thereupon be`
  line `entitled to sue thereon in his own name as if it had been originally given to him instead of to the Judge of`
  line `the Court, and to recover, as trustee for all persons interested, such amount as may be recoverable`
  line thereunder.
obj_root_law_sections_375_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_376:
  sectionId (33885)
  sectionNo (376)
  orderNo 377
  title `Extension of certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_376_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_376_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33885&sectionno=376&orderno=377&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_376_content:
  string
  line `(1) A District Judge may, on the application of the holder of a`
  line `certificate under this Part, extend the certificate to any debt or security not originally specified therein,`
  line `and every such extension shall have the same effect as if the debt or security to which the certificate is`
  line `extended had been originally specified therein.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon the extension of a certificate, powers with respect to the receiving of interest or dividends`
  line `on, or the negotiation or transfer of, any security to which the certificate has been extended may be`
  line `conferred, and a bond or further bond or other security for the purposes mentioned in section 375 may be`
  line `required, in the same manner as upon the original grant of a certificate.`
obj_root_law_sections_376_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_377:
  sectionId (33886)
  sectionNo (377)
  orderNo 378
  title `Forms of certificate and extended certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_377_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_377_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33886&sectionno=377&orderno=378&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_377_content:
  string
  line `Certificates shall be granted and extensions of`
  line `certificates shall be made, as nearly as circumstances admit, in the forms set forth in Schedule VIII.`
obj_root_law_sections_377_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_378:
  sectionId (33887)
  sectionNo (378)
  orderNo 379
  title `Amendment of certificate in respect of powers as to securities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_378_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33887&sectionno=378&orderno=379&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_378_content:
  string
  line `Where a District Judge has`
  line `not conferred on the holder of a certificate any power with respect to a security specified in the certificate,`
  line `or has only empowered him to receive interest or dividends on, or to negotiate or transfer, the security the`
  line `Judge may, on application made by petitioner and on cause shown to his satisfaction, amend the`
  line `certificate by conferring any of the powers mentioned in section 374 or by substituting any one for any`
  line `other of those powers.`
obj_root_law_sections_378_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_379:
  sectionId (33888)
  sectionNo (379)
  orderNo 380
  title `Mode of collecting court-fees on certificates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_379_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_379_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33888&sectionno=379&orderno=380&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_379_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every application for a certificate or for the`
  line `extension of a certificate shall be accompanied by a deposit of a sum equal to the fee payable under the`
  line `Court-Fees Act, 1870 (7 of 1870), in respect of the certificate or extension applied for.`
  line
  line `(2) If the application is allowed, the sum deposited by the applicant shall be expended, under the`
  line `direction of the Judge, in the purchase of the stamp to be used for denoting the fee payable as aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(3) Any sum received under sub-section (1) and not expended under sub-section (2) shall be refunded`
  line `to the person who deposited it.`
obj_root_law_sections_379_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_380:
  sectionId (33889)
  sectionNo (380)
  orderNo 381
  title `Local extent of certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_380_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_380_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33889&sectionno=380&orderno=381&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_380_content:
  string
  line `A certificate under this Part shall have effect`
  line `throughout ^1[India] ^2***.`
  line
  line `^3[This section shall apply in ^3[India] ^4`
  line `after the separation of Burma and Aden from India to`
  line `certificates granted in Burma and Aden before the date of the separation, or after that date in proceedings`
  line `which were pending at that date.]`
  line
  line `^5[It shall also apply in ^3[India] ^6***^7`
  line `after the separation of Pakistan from India to certificates granted`
  line `before the date of the separation, or after that date in proceedings pending at that date in any of the`
  line `territories which on that date constituted Pakistan.]`
obj_root_law_sections_380_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs.by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "the States".`
  line
  line `2. The words of "India" omitted by the A.O. 1950.`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `4. 1st April, 1937.`
  line
  line `5. Added by the A.O. 1948.`
  line
  line `6. The words "of India" omitted by Act 48 of 1952, s. 3 and Schedule II.`
  line
  line `7. 15th August, 1947.`
obj_root_law_sections_381:
  sectionId (33890)
  sectionNo (381)
  orderNo 382
  title `Effect of certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_381_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_381_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33890&sectionno=381&orderno=382&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_381_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Part, the certificate of the District Judge`
  line `shall, with respect to the debts and securities specified therein, be conclusive as against the persons owing`
  line `such debts or liable on such securities, and shall, notwithstanding any contravention of section 370, or`
  line `other defect, afford full indemnity to all such persons as regards all payments made, or dealings had, in`
  line `good faith in respect of such debts or securities to or with the person to whom the certificate was granted.`
obj_root_law_sections_381_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_382:
  sectionId (33891)
  sectionNo (382)
  orderNo 383
  title `Effect of certificate granted or extended by Indian representative in Foreign State and in certain other cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_382_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 1957, s. 2 for s. 382.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33891&sectionno=382&orderno=383&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_382_content:
  string
  line `^1[382. Effect of certificate granted or extended by Indian representative in Foreign State and in`
  line `certain other cases.-- Where a certificate in the form, as nearly as circumstances admit, of Schedule`
  line VIII
  line
  line `(a) has been granted to a resident within a foreign State by an Indian representative accredited to`
  line `that State, or`
  line
  line `(b) has been granted before the commencement of the Part B States (Laws) Act, 1951 (3 of 1951),`
  line `to a resident within any Part B State by a district judge of that State or has been extended by him in`
  line `such form, or`
  line
  line `(c) has been granted after the commencement of the Part B States (Laws) Act, 1951 (3 of 1951),`
  line `to a resident within the State of Jammu and Kashmir by the district judge of that State or has been`
  line `extended by him in such form, the certificate shall, when stamped in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of the Court-Fees Act, 1870 (7 of 1870), with respect to certificates under this Part, have the same`
  line `effect in India as a certificate granted or extended under this Part.]`
obj_root_law_sections_383:
  sectionId (33892)
  sectionNo (383)
  orderNo 384
  title `Revocation of certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_383_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_383_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33892&sectionno=383&orderno=384&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_383_content:
  string
  line `A certificate granted under this Part may be revoked for any of the`
  line `following causes, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) that the proceedings to obtain the certificate were defective in substance;`
  line
  line `(b) that the certificate was obtained fraudulently by the making of a false suggestion, or by the`
  line `concealment from the Court of something material to the case;`
  line
  line `(c) that the certificate was obtained by means of an untrue allegation of a fact essential in point of`
  line `law to justify the grant thereof, though such allegation was made in ignorance or inadvertently;`
  line
  line `(d) that the certificate has become useless and inoperative through circumstances;`
  line
  line `(e) that a decree or order made by a competent Court in a suit or other proceeding with respect to`
  line `effects comprising debts or securities specified in the certificate renders it proper that the certificate`
  line `should be revoked.`
obj_root_law_sections_383_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_384:
  sectionId (33893)
  sectionNo (384)
  orderNo 385
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_384_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_384_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33893&sectionno=384&orderno=385&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_384_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the other provisions of this Part, an appeal shall lie to the High Court`
  line `from an order of a District Judge granting, refusing or revoking a certificate under this Part, and the High`
  line `Court may, if it thinks fit, by its order on the appeal, declare the person to whom the certificate should be`
  line `granted and direct the District judge, on application being made therefore, to grant it accordingly, in super`
  line `session of the certificate, if any, already granted.`
  line
  line `(2) An appeal under sub-section (1) must be preferred within the time allowed for an appeal under the`
  line `Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of1908).`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (1) and to the provisions as to reference to and revision by`
  line `the High Court and as to review of judgment of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), as applied`
  line `by section 141 of that Code, an order of a District Judge under this Part shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_384_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_385:
  sectionId (33894)
  sectionNo (385)
  orderNo 386
  title `Effect on certificate of previous certificate, probate or letters of administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_385_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_385_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33894&sectionno=385&orderno=386&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_385_content:
  string
  line `Save as`
  line `provided by this Act, a certificate granted thereunder in respect of any of the effects of a deceased person`
  line `shall be invalid if there has been a previous grant of such a certificate or of probate or letters of`
  line `administration in respect of the estate of the deceased person and if such previous grant is in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_385_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_386:
  sectionId (33895)
  sectionNo (386)
  orderNo 387
  title `Validation of certain payments made in good faith to holder of invalid certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_386_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_386_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33895&sectionno=386&orderno=387&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_386_content:
  string
  line `Where a certificate under this Part has been superseded or is invalid by reason of the`
  line `certificate having been revoked under section 383,or by reason of the grant of a certificate to a person`
  line `named in an appellate order under section 384, or by reason of a certificate having been previously`
  line `granted, or for any other cause, all payments made or dealings had, as regards debts and securities`
  line `specified in the superseded or invalid certificate, to or with the holder of that certificate in ignorance of its`
  line `super session or invalidity, shall be held good against claims under any other certificate.`
obj_root_law_sections_386_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_387:
  sectionId (33896)
  sectionNo (387)
  orderNo 388
  title `Effect of decisions under this Act, and liability of holder of certificate thereunder.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_387_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_387_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33896&sectionno=387&orderno=388&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_387_content:
  string
  line `No decision under this Part upon any question of right between any parties shall be held to`
  line `bar the trial of the same question in any suit or in any other proceeding between the same parties, and`
  line `nothing in this Part shall be construed to affect the liability of any person who may receive the whole or`
  line `any part of any debt or security, or any interest or dividend on any security, to account therefore to the`
  line `person lawfully entitled thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_387_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_388:
  sectionId (33897)
  sectionNo (388)
  orderNo 389
  title `Investiture of inferior courts with jurisdiction of District Court for purposes of this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_388_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_388_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33897&sectionno=388&orderno=389&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_388_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may by notification in the Official Gazette, invest any court inferior in`
  line `grade to a District Judge with power to exercise the functions of a District Judge under this Part.`
  line
  line `(2) Any inferior court so invested shall, within the local limits of its jurisdiction, have concurrent`
  line `jurisdiction with the District Judge in the exercise of all the powers conferred by this Part upon the`
  line `District Judge, and the provisions of this Part relating to the District Judge shall apply to such an inferior`
  line `court as if it were a District Judge:`
  line
  line `Provided that an appeal from any such order of an inferior court as is mentioned in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 384 shall lie to the District Judge, and not to the High Court, and that the District Judge may, if he`
  line `thinks fit, by his order on the appeal, make any such declaration and direction as that sub-section`
  line `authorises the High Court to make by its order on an appeal from an order of a District Judge.`
  line
  line `(3) An order of a District Judge on an appeal from an order of an inferior Court under the last`
  line `foregoing sub-section shall, subject to the provisions as to reference to and revision by the High Court`
  line `and as to review of judgment of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), as applied by section`
  line `141 of that Code, be final.`
  line
  line `(4) The District Judge may withdraw any proceedings under this Part from an inferior court, and may`
  line `either himself dispose of them or transfer them to another such court established within the local limits of`
  line `the jurisdiction of the District Judge and having authority to dispose of the proceedings.`
  line
  line `(5) A notification under sub-section (1) may specify any inferior court specially or any class of such`
  line `courts in any local area.`
  line
  line `(6) Any Civil Court which for any of the purposes of any enactment is subordinate to, or subject to`
  line `the control of, a District Judge shall, for the purposes of this section, be deemed to be a court inferior in`
  line `grade to a District Judge.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of Central Act 39 of 1925.--In the Indian Succession Act, 1925 (Central Act 39 of`
  line `1925) as in force in the State of Karnataka, section 388 shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 28 of 1978, s. 4].`
obj_root_law_sections_388_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_389:
  sectionId (33898)
  sectionNo (389)
  orderNo 390
  title `Surrender of superseded and invalid certificates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_389_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_389_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33898&sectionno=389&orderno=390&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_389_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a certificate under this Part has`
  line `been superseded or is invalid from any of the causes mentioned in section 386, the holder thereof shall, on`
  line `the requisition of the Court which granted it, deliver it upto that court.`
  line
  line `(2) If he willfully and without reasonable cause omits so to deliver it up, he shall be punishable with`
  line `fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or with imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `three months or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_389_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_390:
  sectionId (33899)
  sectionNo (390)
  orderNo 391
  title `Provisions with respect to certificates under Bombay Regulation VIII of 1827.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_390_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_390_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33899&sectionno=390&orderno=391&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_390_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in Bombay Regulation No. VIII of 1827 the provisions of section 370, subsection (2), section 372, sub-section (1), clause (f), and sections 374, 375, 376, 377, 378, 379, 381, 383,`
  line `384, 387, 388 and 389 with respect to certificates under this Part and applications therefore, and of`
  line `section 317 with respect to the exhibition of inventories and accounts by executors and administrators,`
  line `shall, so far as they can be made applicable, apply, respectively, to certificates granted under that`
  line `Regulation and applications made for certificates thereunder, after the 1st day of May, 1889 and to the`
  line `exhibition of inventories and accounts by the holders of such certificates so granted.`
obj_root_law_sections_390_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_391:
  sectionId (42818)
  sectionNo (391)
  orderNo 392
  title Saving.
  content obj_root_law_sections_391_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_391_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=42818&sectionno=391&orderno=392&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_391_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in Part VIII, Part IX or Part X shall--`
  line
  line `(i) validate any testamentary disposition which would otherwise have been invalid;`
  line
  line `(ii) invalidate any such disposition which would otherwise have been valid;`
  line
  line `(iii) deprive any person of any right of maintenance to which he would otherwise have been`
  line `entitled; or`
  line
  line `(iv) affect the Administrator Generals Act, 1913 (3 of 1913).`
obj_root_law_sections_391_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_392:
  sectionId (33900)
  sectionNo (392)
  orderNo 393
  title [Repealed.].
  content `[Repealed.]--Rep. by the Repealing Act, 1927 (12 of 1927), s. 2 and Schedule.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_392_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879&sectionId=33900&sectionno=392&orderno=393&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00058_192539_1523349789879
obj_root_law_sections_392_footnotes:
  string
  line
